project.title: SUN EATER - fanart
project.description:
This is the fanart for Dylan Sprouse's comic book named "Sun Eater" . Here is the short description of the comic:
"Sun Eater is a twelve-issue saga that takes place in ninth century Norway, where a drug-addled warrior sacrifices his leg to the Gods.  In return he is fused with a parasitic beast, giving him the power to rescue his son from his sworn enemies—history’s first Norwegian king and his five personal guards. The result is a grim and bloody adventure—a dark metaphor for drug addiction, selfishness, and the children it affects."
Pretty awesome stuff, make sure to check it out.

project.title: UE4 Practice 01
project.description: My first try and quick practice in Unreal Engine 4, Megascans and Quixel Mixer. These dudes are really great! One day of work on this small scene. Mostly tried myself in the creation of materials, practice with Mixer and Megascans Bridge, material blending for vertex painting, setup the lighting to get a cinematic look, light baking, and other cool features of Unreal Engine. I've used mostly Megascans assets and some of the assets from Unreal Marketplace. I had real fun playing and assembling these assets together in one scene. Hope you like it, cheers!

project.title: Assassin's Creed Valhalla - Giants Boss Fights
project.description:
At Ubisoft Barcelona we had the pleasure to work on the boss fights for the two dreamworlds in Assassin's Creed Valhalla main game. The art team had the opportunity to fully develop the Giants Arena's look and mood as well as the visual direction for all the in-combat VFX and lighting. 

As a Lead Artist my main focus was to keep this content consistent with the rest of the dreamworlds art direction. Under the supervision of Raphael Lacoste, AC Brand Art Director, I oversaw my team's work from concept to level art as well as lighting and FX to make sure we reached the high standards expected in an Assassin's Creed title. I was also in constant communication with other disciplines and studios involved in the realisation or these encounters to make sure we had a fluent and visually appealing experience.

Special mention to the job done by Pau Treserra and Pablo Ruano who owned these arenas through all their development.
https://www.artstation.com/pautre
https://www.artstation.com/garf

I would also like to highlight the amazing job done by Daniel Arriaga in the stunning combat VFX that trully made this bosses shine.
https://www.artstation.com/daniel_arriaga

Speciall thanks also to:
https://www.artstation.com/csthorpe
https://www.artstation.com/massimilianoitaliano
https://www.artstation.com/guillaumedm

Assassin's Creen Valhalla is the result of a huge team effort across many Ubisoft Studios in charge of multiple visual aspects such us regions, locations, biomes, lighting, FX, materials assets and props. This could have not been achieved without the involvement of ALL the art teams. It has been a pleasure to work with such talented teams and artists!
